14 Apr 2015 04:08








Mobile Task Force D12
附加记录：    

All I can imagine now is Eminen and co. working for the Foundation, goddamnit kaktus

On topic: overall, I thought this was pretty damn solid. Very reminiscent of skips like SCP-1919, which are some of my favorite on the site. There's something awfully horrifying about exploration-based skips like these, as each log slowly amps up the horror, each seemingly disparate in terms of content but linked by common motifs that drive home the ominous feel magnificently. The buildup of tension was fantastic and several segments of the logs had me recoiling in horror- in particular the last part of the first log with D12-2 and D12-5- which is something that almost no skips have done.

However, I do have some gripes with it. The part where the drone finds Dr. Bright seems like name-dropping for the sake of name-dropping. At first it terrified me because of the implications it carried, but it didn't really take them anywhere. Are there now two Dr. Brights in our reality? Is our Dr. Bright actually from that reality and completely foreign to ours? It could've been the creepiest part of the skip but I feel it wasn't used to its full potential. The ending was also pretty meh, as mistreatment of humanoid skips by cruel Foundation members is a plot point that has been done many times and no longer really affects me that much.

I am willing to look past these minor problems I had just because of how wonderfully unsettling this is. You done good kaktus








And if the whole world is crashing down fall through space out of mind with me.






