Ok, so. I love the idea of a Site kicked across reality. I like the world-building of the alternate universe to an extent, although the idea of a less-ethical Foundation equivalent is depressing as all get-out. I like the random Jack Bright appearance, and think it would have been deeply amusing if they had found him. The cognitohazard integration was interesting.

However, you also made me slog through multiple pages of MTF-in-an-anomalous-building snuff fic. That's just not interesting to me on its own terms anymore, and I don't think the storybuilding-per-wordcount ratio in those segments was even remotely worth it.

I guess I'm ultimately downvoting.







